8. The &agr;-amylase-resistant polysaccharide as claimed in one of the preceding claims obtainable by a process comprising the following steps: 
a) producing a suspension or dispersion from water-insoluble poly(1 ,4-&agr;-D-glucans) and water; 
b) warming the suspension or dispersion; 
c) cooling the resultant gel and retrogradation of the gel at a temperature which is lower than the temperature of the heated gel; and 
d) if appropriate drying the resultant product.

9. The &agr;-amylase-resistant polysaccharide as claimed in one of claims 1 to 7 obtainable by a process comprising the following steps: 
a) producing a suspension or dispersion from water-insoluble poly(1,4-&agr;-D-glucans) and water; 
b) freezing the resultant suspension or dispersion; 
c) retrogradation; 
d) thawing the mass obtained by step c); and 
e) if appropriate drying the mass obtained by step d) or dewatering the resultant mass.

10. A process for producing &agr;-amylase-resistant polysaccharides having high RS content comprising the following steps; 
a) producing a suspension or dispersion from water-insoluble poly(1,4-&agr;-D-glucans) and water; 
b) warming the suspension or dispersion; 
c) cooling the resultant gel and retrogradation of the gel at a temperature which is lower than the temperature of the heated gel; and 
d) if appropriate drying or dewatering the resultant product.
